Inspect and manage DocType definitions.

Examples:
  weg doctype list                       # List custom doctypes
  weg doctype list myapp                 # List doctypes in app
  weg doctype show User                  # Show DocType structure
  weg doctype reload myapp module MyDoc  # Reload from disk

Usage:
  weg doctype [command]

Available Commands:
  list        List DocTypes
  reload      Reload DocType from disk
  show        Show DocType structure

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for doctype

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg doctype [command] --help" for more information about a command.
